5. Updates all three variables to new values to trigger recomputation
6. Gets the updated values after the changes
7. Returns a snapshot containing all four results (initial and updated for both expressions)

The function demonstrates how logical operators work with reactive values and how expressions automatically recompute when their dependencies change.

